Working closely with the Manager, Data Management and Planned Reporting
(DMPR), the senior information officer is responsible for contributing to the
maintenance, development and implementation of various performance reporting
methods and systems to monitor and project performance data pertaining to the
topics of employment, small business and vocational education and training
(VET), and to fulfil internal, external, and corporate reporting requirements.
The role requires a high skill set in the use of data collection, data
management and data analysis technologies. As a member of the DMPR team you
will collaborate with fellow team members and clients at varying levels across
the department to deliver data collection and reporting products that support
the strategic direction of DESBT.

** As Senior Information Officer, you will specifically: **   
• Extract, analyse, interpret, and present complex data sets for distribution
to internal and external clients in response to on-demand requests and regular
internal, external, and corporate reporting requirements.  
• Develop and maintain business intelligence and data visualisation solutions
to present departmental data and statistics in an accessible and user-friendly
manner for distribution to internal and external clients.  
• Develop and maintain data collection processes in accordance with
departmental standards and procedures.  
• Provide technical assistance and expert advice to staff on data-related
procurement, projects and the appropriate use, interpretation, and
presentation of data.  
• Maintain knowledge of best practice data management techniques to ensure
data presentation and sharing meets customer needs.  
• Liaise with other departmental officers, other government departments and
the wider community to manage expectations, gain a broader knowledge of user
needs/desires and to identify data sharing opportunities.

We're committed to appointing the best-suited person for each role. This
includes considering equity, diversity, respect, and inclusion needs within
our agency. We believe that these elements are essential for the success of
our team, and we strongly encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to
apply. If you require any reasonable adjustments to fully participate in the
recruitment process, please do not hesitate to contact the designated contact
for the vacancy.

